content.text: Find the number of different ways this can be done
The 8 pieces of music are then arranged in order
Find the number of different arrangements possible
The band has 15 members. Three members are chosen at random to be the treasurer, secretary and agent
Find the number of ways in which this can be done
A band can play 25 different pieces of music. From these pieces of music, 8 are to be selected for a concert

The graph of \(y = \mathrm{f}(x)\) meets the \(y\)-axis at the point \((0, - 1)\), has a period of \(120^{\circ}\) and an amplitude of 5
